

## **How Does DeFi Work?**

Todayâ€™s global economy relies on large, centralized financial institutions to handle transactions and manage money. This often prevents new users from accessing financial markets and makes it difficult for developers to create new financial products and offerings.

In contrast, `DeFi` uses public blockchains like Ethereum to create a global, peer-to-peer financial system.


![](data:image/png;base64,)

Traditional Finance vs DeFi

The key difference here is that in DeFi, all transactions are made public via an explorer. Furthermore, the code is open for anyone to see and verify, which builds trust and reduces costs associated with intermediaries.

From a developerâ€™s perspective, the biggest advantage of DeFi is permissionless composability.

This means a developer can combine logic from different DeFi apps together like building blocks to create new financial products and services without needing special permission!
